node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 31, 2021. May be an image of dog and text that says 'ANIMAL ABUSE STATISTICS 2021 SWIPE'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 31, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, dog and text that says 'Statistics of animal abuse reveal that every 60 seconds, one animal suffers abuse. Close to 65% of all abused animals are dogs based on stats about animal abuse. There are two types of animal abuse: passive and active cruelty.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 31, 2021. May be an image of animal and text that says 'Every year, more than 115 million animals in the world are used for laboratory experiments. Every year, US labs abuse more than 19,000 cats. Denmark slaughtered 15-17 million animals for mink fur that tested positive for Covid-19.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 31, 2021. May be an image of cat and text that says 'Approximately 75,000 dogs are tortured in US labs every year. It's estimated that the lifetime prevalence of animal abuse in US adults is 1.8% according to domestic animal abuse statistics.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 31, 2021. May be an image of cat and text that says 'Statistics on animal cruelty reveal that very year, more than 10 million animals die from abuse in the US alone. Every year, more than 6.5 million animals enter animal shelters according to animal abuse statistics in the United States.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 31, 2021. May be an image of dog and text that says 'The latest animal abuse stats reveal that each year, the US kills over 3 million mink for fur. Over the last decade, there've been 483 drug- positive Greyhounds in Florida alone.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 31, 2021. May be an image of animal and text that says 'On average, 250,000 animals every year are victims of animal hoarding. Statistics on animal abuse reveal that there are over 10,000 puppy mills in the United States.'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 06, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'GREACE AND TURKEY ARE ON FIRE SWIPE'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 06, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Greece is facing one of its worst heatwaves in decades and the country remains on high alert as it continues to battle blazes across the country. Heat warnings have also been issued for Bosnia and Herzegovina, Bulgaria, Italy, Romania, Serbia and Turkey. Deadly wildfires have swept across parts of Turkey in recent days and forced the evacuation of tourist resorts.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 06, 2021. May be an image of child, sky, ocean and text that says 'Residents of the Greek capital, Athens have been warned to stay indoors with their windows closed because of poor air quality after a wildfire raged Tuesday in the suburbs.north of the capital. The extreme heat forced the Ministry of Culture to close the Acropolis and other ancient sites from noon to 5 p.m. local this week.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on August 06, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'In the past 3 days, dozens of towns and villages in Greece have been evacuated as protracted heatwave and strengthening winds fueled more than 150 wildfires and scientists say the destruction in just the last 72 hours exceeds 50% of the average area burnt in previous years! In Turkey 8 people have died, tens of thousands have been evacuated and thousands of animals have perished and despite these wildfires burning 7x more land this year than any year in decades, this country has NO firefighting planes, so we must send them help!'.

TURKEY IS ON FIRE! This needs to be brought to EVERYONE'S attention! node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of fire, sky and text that says 'TURKEY IS ON FIRE SWIPE'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of sky and text that says 'More than 60 wildfires have broken out across 17 provinces on Turkey's Aegean and Mediterranean coasts this week, killing at least 4 people along with thousands of farm animals and sending 60 more people to the hospital as their homes burned down வ்கி்்ன் က် ជញ ചോടት'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of fire, outdoors and text that says 'So far, 18 villages have been evacuated and 35 aircrafts, 457 vehicles and 4,000 personnel have been involved in the firefighting efforts, as separate wildfires raged in the provinces of Osmaniye, Kayseri, Kocaeii, Adana, Mersin and Kutahya.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on July 30, 2021. May be an image of outdoors and text that says 'Turkey has battled a series of disasters caused by extreme weather conditions this summer, including flash floods last week that killed 6 people in the Black Sea region. These disasters have been devastating to the wildlife in Turkey, killing countless innocent animals and destroying their homes'.

node.text: More than two million children under five in Yemen do not have enough food to eat, with over 2,200 on the brink of starving to death. LETS HELP THESE CHILDREN❤️🌲🌎

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎LETS TALK ABOUT YEMEN ㅇ人פ SWIPE >>‎'‎.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Yemen is the largest humanitarian crisis in the world, with around 21 million people in need of humanitarian assistance, including more than 11 million children.'.
Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of 8 people, people standing, outdoors and text that says 'In Yemen, a child dies every 10 minutes from preventable causes'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of child and text that says 'Ever since armed conflict escalated in Yemen in March 2015, the country has been edging toward social and economic collapse. Eighty percent of the population 24 million people, including roughly 12 million children are in need of humanitarian assistance.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of child and text that says 'Increasing food insecurity has pushed the country to the brink of famine. Cholera is endemic. Over 2 million children are malnourished. At least 2 million children have been driven from their homes by violence.'.

Photo by Plant A Tree Co. on June 27, 2021. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'The COVID-19 pandemic has only compounded the country's suffering, further straining an already fragile health system, disrupting education for millions of children and leaving them increasingly vulnerable to exploitation and abuse.'.
